The paper discusses a dimensionality reduction tool used for data visualization and manifold learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and data science. The paper also proposes a new method for efficient computation of geodesic distances, which is a topic in computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
